                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d730">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/2347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-06T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 6, 1935—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>196. Your 349, November 6, 11 a.m. Department of Commerce regularly and
                    ordinarily collects and publishes careful and full details of American import
                    and export trade with all countries. Hence the full details of our trade with
                    belligerents will be available promptly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
